Hungarian Cabinet Orders IPads for Ministers, Vilaggazdasag Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-04-27T06:14:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/hungarian-cabinet-orders-ipads-for-ministers-vilaggazdasag-says.html
Hungary’s government ordered  Apple
Inc. (AAPL) ’s iPad2 for all ministers, state secretaries and their
deputies,  Vilaggazdasag  reported, without citing anyone.  The government plans to spend about 16 million forint
($88,745) on about 90 tablets, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz in Budapest at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net . 